# Chunks — Memory Drill

## Purpose

Drill high-frequency phrases as atomic units. Do not decompose into grammar. Prompt with English → produce full Greek phrase from memory.

Target: 3 seconds for social phrases, 5 seconds for longer openers.

## Phase 1 core set

### Social ritual (simplest, drill first)
| English | Greek |
|---------|-------|
| Hello / Hi | Γεια σου / Γεια σας (formal) |
| Good morning | Καλημέρα |
| Good evening | Καλησπέρα |
| Good night | Καληνύχτα |
| Goodbye | Αντίο / Γεια |
| See you later | Τα λέμε |
| Thank you | Ευχαριστώ |
| You're welcome / Please | Παρακαλώ |
| Excuse me / Sorry | Συγγνώμη |
| How are you? (informal) | Τι κάνεις; |
| I'm fine | Είμαι καλά |

### Comprehension survival
| English | Greek |
|---------|-------|
| I don't understand | Δεν καταλαβαίνω |
| I don't know | Δεν ξέρω |
| Can you speak more slowly? | Μπορείτε να μιλάτε πιο αργά; |
| How do you say...? | Πώς λέγεται...;  |
| What does ... mean? | Τι σημαίνει ...;  |

### Sentence starters (frames, not full sentences — drill the opener)
| English prompt | Greek opener |
|----------------|--------------|
| My name is... | Με λένε... |
| I would like... | Θα ήθελα... |
| Where is...? | Πού είναι...;  |
| How much is...? | Πόσο κάνει...;  |
| Can I...? | Μπορώ να...;  |
| I need to... | Πρέπει να... |
| I want to... | Θέλω να... |
| Do you have...? | Έχετε...;  |

## Drill format

**Forward**: English → Greek (type full phrase, including punctuation optional)
**Recognition**: Greek → English (multiple choice or typed)

No paradigm table. No person/number selector. Pure sequential recall.

## Grouping

- Group A: Social ritual (11 items) — drill to automaticity before B
- Group B: Comprehension survival (5 items)
- Group C: Sentence starters (8 items) — lowest priority, learner may already have these from tutor

## Notes

- Accept minor variants: Αντίο / Γεια both valid for goodbye
- "Γεια σου" vs "Γεια σας" distinction: informal vs formal — could teach as separate items or accept both
- Sentence starters are frames — drill just the opener chunk ("Θα ήθελα"), not a full sentence completion
- If learner's tutor work has covered these already, this drill surfaces which are NOT yet automatic vs which can be deprioritised
